**Defining the Data Model (Database Design)**

*Authorized Users*
user_id (integer) - internal ID student will type/scan
student_hash (text) - system will hash student ID 
role (text) - admin/user - students are "user" / employees are "admin"
name (text) - student will type in their full name (**ON HOLD**)

*Visit Log*
session_id (integer) - system will document student's independent session IDs
student_hash (text) - system will document student hashed ID
check_in_time (datetime) - system will document student's check-in time
check_out_time (datetime) - system will document student's check-out time
duration (integer) - system will document how long the student has been checked-in

*System Events*
event_id (integer) - system will recognize event ID by a list of possible outcomes
timestamp (datetime) - system will generate a timestamp of event
event_type (text) - system will recognize event type by a list of possible outcomes
description (text) - system will describe the events
- "scan_error"
- "unauthorized_attempt"
- "system_start"





**System States**
BOOT → IDLE → SCAN_DETECTED → VALIDATE → AUTHORIZE
         ↓
      CHECK_IN / CHECK_OUT
         ↓
        IDLE






**Hardware Setup**

*Core Hardware*
- Raspberry Pi
- RFID or barcode reader
- LED indicators
- buzzer
- display (optional)
- power supply
- enclosure

*Connections Example*
RFID Reader → USB
LED Green → GPIO17
LED Red → GPIO27
Buzzer → GPIO22
Display → I2C



